Redescription. Carapace (
Fig. 21 a
) very much wider than long (CB/CL = 2.1 ), relatively convex, microscopic granules regularly on carapace, some slightly larger granules on epibranchial region, usually in transverse row; transverse row of small granules on posterior region, extending parallel to posterior margin, granules extensively lined. Regions well defined; furrows defining gastric, epibranchial regions remarkably deep. Front narrow, about 0.16 times as wide as carapace; anterior edge smooth, very slightly concave, not bi-lobed, frontal furrow faint.
